<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,684,999]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,793,819]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</emphasis>
So far, two of the three subspecies of this species viz., 
<taxonomicName authority="gloriosa (Erschoff, 1874)" authorityName="gloriosa (Erschoff" authorityYear="1874" baseAuthorityName="Erschoff" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[935,1355,792,819]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Hypopta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="gloriosa" subSpecies="gloriosa">
<emphasis box="[935,1162,792,818]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">H. gloriosa gloriosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Erschoff, N. G." box="[1177,1346,792,819]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 127" refId="ref73538" refString="Erschoff, N. G. (1874) Lepidoptera. In: Fedchenko, A. P. (Ed.), Reise in Turkestan (1874 - 1879). Memoires de la Societe des amis de sciences naturelles, Moscou, 11 (2), pp. 1 - 127. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1874">Erschoff, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Watkins &amp; Buxton, 1921" authorityName="Watkins &amp; Buxton" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Hypopta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="gloriosa" subSpecies="mesopotamicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">H. gloriosa mesopotamicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Watkins, H. T. G. &amp; Buxton, R. A." box="[434,720,828,855]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="184 - 186" refId="ref80463" refString="Watkins, H. T. G. &amp; Buxton, R. A. (1921) Moths of Mesopotamia and N. W Persia. Part H. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 28, 184 - 186." type="journal article" year="1921">Watkins &amp; Buxton, 1921</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, have been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1065,829,855]" name="Iran" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yakovlev, R. V." box="[1081,1269,828,855]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 129" refId="ref81797" refString="Yakovlev, R. V. (2011 a) Catalogue of the Family Cossidae of the Old World. Neue Entomologische Nachrichten, 66, 1 - 129." type="journal article" year="2011">
<taxonomicName box="[1081,1189,828,854]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" status="subfam. n." subFamily="Yakovlev">Yakovlev</taxonomicName>
2011a
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Wieser, C. &amp; Huemer, P. &amp; Stangelmaier, G." box="[151,376,864,891]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="52 - 81" refId="ref80533" refString="Wieser, C., Huemer, P., &amp; Stangelmaier, G. (2001) Schmetterlinge (Lepidoptera). In: Wieser, B. &amp; Wieser, C. (Eds.), Nordiran. Ergebnisse einer zoologischen Exkursion. Carinthia II, Klagenfurt, 192 / 112, 52 - 81." type="journal article" year="2001">
Wieser 
<emphasis box="[236,286,864,890]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Staudinger, 1899" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1899" box="[388,832,864,891]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Hypopta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="gloriosa" subSpecies="laudabilis">
<emphasis box="[388,635,864,890]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">H. gloriosa laudabilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Staudinger, O." box="[642,832,864,891]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="157 - 159" refId="ref79424" refString="Staudinger, O. (1899) Neue palaarktische Lepidopteren. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 12, 157 - 159. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9446" type="journal article" year="1899">Staudinger, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was reported from NE 
<collectingCountry box="[1096,1141,865,891]" name="Iran" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1155,1327,864,891]" country="Iran" name="Golestan" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Golestan Prov.</collectingRegion>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[1337,1437,864,890]" country="Iran" name="Golestan" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Golestan</collectingRegion>
National Park [Alagol, Dasht]; 
<collectingRegion box="[498,745,900,927]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Shomali" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">North Khorasan Prov.</collectingRegion>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[754,854,900,926]" country="Iran" name="Golestan" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Golestan</collectingRegion>
National Park [Almeh]), but the authors believe that this subspecies is only distributed in Arabian Peninsula and the nominal subspecies are found in the northern and central parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[326,375,973,999]" name="Iran" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
